com.misc.common.moplaf.dbsynch

Interface Table

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    TableImpl

    public interface Table
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject
    A representation of the model object 'Table'.

    A concrete Table is a class mapped on a possibly filtered database table.

    A Table supports metadata, that will allow the framework to synchronize (up or down) the object data with the db data:

    • getTableName(): the name of the table
    • getKeyColumns(): the columns of the table that are part of the key
    • getDataColumns(): the columns of the table that are NOT part of the key
    • getWhereClause(): the condition that will be used to filter the rows up synched
    • getParamDbSynchUnitAttributes() : the attributes in the synch unit to be used as values in the where clause
    The metadata is part of the state of the Table. It must be provided
    • either at run time by the user,
    • or at design time, by implementing method refreshMetaData().

    Following information about the execution of the synchronization is returned

    • getLastSynchDown() : timestamp of the last synchronization down
    • getLastSynchUp() : timestamp of the last synchronization up
    • getNumberOfRows(): number of rows present.

    The following features are supported:

    • Synch Unit
    • Columns
    • Key Columns
    • Data Columns
    • Table Name
    • Where Clause
    • Param Db Synch Unit Attributes
    • Rows
    • Select Sql Statement
    • Insert Sql Statement
    • Update Sql Statement
    • Delete Sql Statement
    • Number Of Rows
    • Last Synch Down
    • Last Synch Up
    See Also:
    DbSynchPackage.getTable()
